Jeremy Barr

communications.subject: Virginia Freedom of Information Act Request: Club Communications
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Virginia Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

TO AVOID UNNECESSARY DELAYS IN PROCESSING, I REQUEST NOW THAT ANY ESTIMATED COST TO FILL MY REQUEST BE PROVIDED.

YOU DO NOT NEED TO ASK ME IF I WANT YOU TO PREPARE A COST ESTIMATE IF THERE IS ONE.

I am requesting copies of:

1. Communications and responses to and from the Commandant's Office to all Student Clubs/organizations (extracurricular activities and clubs, to include club sports) subject to General Order 67 in the last 30 days regarding the charters for those clubs/organizations as well as any responses including all attachments.

2. The Minutes and approval for each club/student organization by the Cadet Extracurricular Activities Board (CEAB) as required by General Order 67 for the past three academic years including the current academic year.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tom Nash, a citizen of Virginia, in coordination with Anonymous.

communications.subject: Virginia Freedom of Information Act Request: Virginia Freedom of Information Act request
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Virginia Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

To whom it may concern:

Pursuant to the Colorado Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

-- Copies of the “stop-work orders” issued to the university by a federal agency
-- Copies of the correspondence, including but not limited to emails messages, email attachments, text messages, video chat messages, and voicemails, between the university and project leads and principal investigators affected by these “stop-work orders”
-- Copies of any and all correspondence, including but not limited to emails messages, email attachments, text messages, video chat messages, and voicemails, between the federal agency and the university regarding these “stop-work orders”
-- Descriptions of the specific projects and/ or programs impacted by the “stop-work orders”
-- A list of the project leads and principal investigators affected by these “stop-work” orders

Please waive applicable fees; this information is being sought for newsgathering purposes in the public interest. As we are making this request as journalists and the information is timely, we also ask that you expedite processing for this request. If I can provide any clarification that will help expedite the processing of this request, please contact me directly.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,
Nicole Einbinder

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tom Nash, a citizen of Virginia, in coordination with Nicole Einbinder.
